race.comment: SILENT DIVA (8) never got into the race on resumption at Belmont but looks primed for a much better run this time around. Pike replaces the apprentice hoop and she's drawn for a much better run today from an inside draw. Can build on the fresh run and return to winning ways. STRAPPING PROPHET (2) flew home over 1200m at Belmont first-up when jumping the race favourite. He can sit closer today from a better draw as well as the slight rise in trip. Closed off nicely last start and he looks a big threat with plenty of upside. GOLDEN KATHLEEN (1) won impressively here two back before finishing strongly last start to be 0.6L off the winner. Been a while without a win, but she's knocking on the door and has to be included. HOBA METEOR (7) just missed last start behind a progressive type and that figure stacks up in this event. PAT'S LAST BANG (6) looks better suited back to a race like this and is not to be discounted.
